*Debuggability* &lt;/pre&gt;&lt;tt&gt;To improve debuggability, developers should be able to set breakpoints &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;directly in their code where the clipboardchange event listener is &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;registered, using the Sources tool as with any other event. &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Additionally, clipboardchange will be available alongside other &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;clipboard-related events—such as copy, cut, and paste—in the &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;“Clipboard” section of Event Listener Breakpoints within the Sources &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;tool. &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;pre style="margin: 0em;"&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;tt&gt;*Will this feature be supported on all six Blink platforms (Windows, &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Mac, Linux, ChromeOS, Android, and Android WebView)?* &lt;/tt&gt;&lt;pre style="margin: 0em;"&gt; Yes
